05/02/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania reported a record trade deficit of 5.59 billion euros for 2003, overshooting the government's targets by nearly one billion.
The figure represents a 40 per cent leap from the 2002 deficit of 3.98 billion.
In other news, Prime Minister Adrian Nastase complained Wednesday (4 February) that Romania has been "ambushed" on the issue of foreign adoptions.
Emma Nicholson, a powerful European Parliament member, wrote a report slamming Bucharest for allowing 105 children to be adopted in Italy.
She called on the European Commission to suspend accession talks with Romania.
(AFP - 04/02/04)
